abstract: >
  Eye_lean is a Unity + Python toolkit for collecting and analyzing
  eye-tracking data from VR head-mounted displays. It ships a
  calibrator with per-user profile correction, a deterministic-replay
  system that reproduces recordings frame-accurately, a real-time
  multi-detector cognitive-load monitor (RIPA2 default plus
  Butterworth / FFT / DWT LF-HF alternatives), and a researcher
  template (Skeleton) for building custom VR behavioral experiments.
